diet and exercise question before setting off on an intensive exercise regime ie bicycling over miles in a day what nutritional dietary planning would need to take place before and after the event to stay maintain health and keep intensity for a fit year old male wow that's a lot of biking firstly good luck secondly eat plenty of carbs beforehand and get plenty of zinc and vitamin c because that sort of exertion is going to kill your immune system you'll need more calories than usual for about a week before the event afterwards get lots of protein you'll need to repair your body torn muscles and all that stuff keep the vitamin c up to boost your immune system and replacement carbs are also vital try energy drinks gels during and shortly after the event they are designed for runners to keep them fuelled up Dieting Atkins Nutritional Approach Nutrition Low-carbohydrate diet Marathon (sport) Dietary fiber Anorexia nervosa Veganism Tocopherol Calorie Alzheimer's disease Life extension Milk Calorie restriction Zinc Vitamin Protein Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Osteoporosis Vegetarian nutrition Vitamin C Common cold Healthy eating Stomach cancer Exercise Malnutrition Breastfeeding Obesity Chronic fatigue syndrome Fecal incontinence Egg (food) Human skin color Vegetarianism South Beach diet Omega-3 fatty acid Coronary heart disease Bicycle Cancer Insulin Raw food diet Food guide pyramid Fancy rat Psoriasis Multiple sclerosis Retinol Osteoarthritis Cirrhosis Coeliac disease Soybean Fasting Traumatic brain injury Dietary supplement Herpes simplex virus Hamster Clinical depression Mosquito Creatine Carbohydrate Diabetes mellitus Sugar substitute Rickets Scar Adjustable gastric band Scientology beliefs and practices Nutrient Tlingit Golden rice Gout Vitamin K Natural Hygiene Cyanocobalamin Vitamin D Eye Nuclear weapon design Glucocorticoid Semen Anemia Energy Guinea pig Medicine Paleolithic diet Weight Watchers Equine conformation Cholesterol Testosterone Spider Signal transduction M